call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Young (ATL) throws the ball out of bounds.
Westbrook (WAS) briefly grasps Bogdanovic's (ATL) arm during the drive and does not affect his ability to defend.
Replay review showed Capela (ATL) is last to make contact with the loose ball prior to it going out of bounds.
Len (WAS) makes incidental contact to Capela's (ATL) arm during the rebound.
Bogdanovic (ATL) makes incidental contact to Westbrook's (WAS) arm after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) deflects the loose ball from Len (WAS) during the rebound.
Collins (ATL) makes incidental contact to Len's (WAS) arm after the release of his shot attempt near the rim.
Collins (ATL) delivers contact to Len's (WAS) head as he attempts to gather the loose ball.

Bogdanovic (ATL) makes incidental contact with Westbrook's (WAS) head after securing the loose ball. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Len (WAS) engages and disengages with Collins (ATL) during the screen.
Capela (ATL) cleanly blocks Westbrook (WAS) during his driving shot attempt.
Len (WAS) slightly extends his arm into Collins' (ATL) body off ball and does not affect his ability to defend.
Capela (ATL) makes incidental contact to Neto's (WAS) body after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (WAS) commits the take foul on Hill (ATL), but the foul is given to Len (WAS).
Len (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bogdanovic (ATL), collapses his arm and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Bertans (WAS) commits a take foul on Huerter (ATL).
